SUPPORT AND RESISTANCE SnR is an indicator in the naked chart that is used to analyze price movements in the market. To identify SnR you have to deepen the knowledge of Market Structure Support (buy) Support occurs in the area where the price started to rise before making a retracement and resuming the rise. Usually this support zone will be in the LOW area Resistance (sell) Resistance occurs in the area where the price begins to decline before making a correction and resuming the decline. Usually the resistance zone will be in the HIGH area. P/S: If the area has 2 rejections either ascending or descending, it can be said to be an SnR zone. But it depends on the strength of the timeframe used
